  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "### Description\nTeku currently keeps all non-finalized blocks in memory.  When finalization is delayed, this significantly increases the memory requirements, often leading to out-of-memory errors.\n\nTeku should limit the number of blocks it keeps in memory and handle reloading non-finalized blocks from disk when required.\n\nThis work relates to Issue #1976\n",
